*Freshwater ecosystems are under severe pressure. These habitats are geographically constrained causing impacts to accumulate. Between NBA 2018 and 2024, freshwater fishes have remained among the most threatened vertebrate groups in South Africa. Waterbirds, dependent on freshwater habitats are declining, with several species becoming more threatened since 2015. Physical modification of rivers and wetlands, invasive alien species and climate change continue to accelerate declines*.

![Free-flowing Tra-Tra river within the Doring River system, in the Western Cape province, historically hosting high numbers of Clanwilliam sandfish (*Labeo seeberi*). Today 98% of the river is invaded by invasive alien black bass species (*Micropterus* spp) and bluegill (*Lepomis macrochirus*). (Â© Jeremy Shelton)](./imgs/fw_img_1.png){fig-align="center"}

