<img src="./imgs/sp_fw_4.png" style="width:100%; object-fit: cover; border-radius:10px; margin: 0"/>

<figcaption>Red-swamp crayfish (*Procambarus clarkia*), was a candidate for eradication in 2018, when it was first reported as part of the NBA 2018. However, in 2018 it was only known from the two localised sites in Mpumalanga and Free State, now it has been detected in the Western Cape province in 2025. (Â©Â LeonÂ Barkhuizen)</figcaption>

